   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0026-0002" class="document">the council minutes of 9 Dec.</a> enclosed in <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0026-0001" class="document">Dinwiddie to GW, 10 Dec. 1756</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0038-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0038-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0006-0002" class="document">the council minutes of 15 Nov.</a> enclosed in <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0006-0001" class="document">Dinwiddie to GW, 16 Nov. 1756</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0038-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0038-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Dinwiddie quoted the paragraph from Loudoun in <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0026-0001" class="document">his to GW, 10 Dec. 1756</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0038-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0038-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>John Kirkpatrick, a Scot who had been living in Alexandria, was GWs secretary.</p>

